infos.info: In his book, Music Radio, Jim Cox writes that Vallee Varieties was aka the Sealtest Show. - Hickerson writes that the Rudy Vallee Show was also known as: - Fleischmann Hour and Sunshine Hour 10/24/29-7/16/36 - Royal Gelatin Hour 8/6/36-9/28/39 - Vallee Varieties sometimed during 3/7/40-7/1/43 (and developed into Sealtest Village Store). - From the OTTER files, we get that the program was known as Johnny Presents during 9/10/46-3/4/47 when the program was sponsored by Philip Morris. - From Archives of the Airways, the 1929-39 run was called The Fleischmann (Yeast) Hour, then The Royal Gelatin Hour, then Palace Theater of the Air.
In 1930 the show became known as The Rudy Vallee Show.
Developed into the Sealtest Village Store.
